rComments: This was a tough class, but  Dr. Menzies is very knowledgable and does a decent job at teaching the information. He's very caring and responds well to emails.

Bland and boring at explaining topics and lecture material, slides aren't organized and very packed with information. LOTS of memorization. Unfortunately, this class is mandatory for HSS students so if you can, take it with another prof.

HSS2305 is a hard course. Read the textbook chapters before lectures and make sure you know the pathways, molecular structures, and slide details intimately and you will do well. His classes are important because the material takes a lot of repetition to memorize and he will answer questions on what you need to know. Slides sometimes disorganized.
